    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-10-17T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-10-17T13:00:00-05:00" n="663"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d663">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">394.31/10–1751: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Belgium</hi> (<gloss type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Millard</hi>
                    </gloss>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brussels</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-10-17T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 17, 1951—7 p. m</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>536. Ref (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss> 525, rptd info Ottawa 105, <gloss
                        target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss> Geneva Gatt 91 [<hi rend="italic">97</hi>],
                    Paris 2249, Oct 16; (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) <gloss target="#t_Deptel1"
                        >Deptel</gloss> sent Geneva Gatt 94, rptd info Brussels 518, Paris 2231,
                    Ottawa 103, Oct 15.</p>
                <pb facs="1512" n="1496" xml:id="pg_1496"/>
                <p>Discussed with Acting Foreign Minister Meurice today substance reftel (<hi
                        rend="italic">b</hi>) and left with him memo embodying points covered.<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d663fn1">For text, see enclosure 1 to Brussels despatch 548,
                        November 6, 1951, <ref target="#pg_1504">p. 1504</ref>.</note> Stressed
                    particularly that this was in confirmation discussion already held Geneva by US
                    del with Belg del <gloss target="#t_GATT1">GATT</gloss>. Also that US Govt
                    position was among other things that Belg dollar import restrictions not
                    regarded as essential element in solution <gloss target="#t_EPU1">EPU</gloss>
                    problem on basis US Govt understanding of present circumstances and that other
                    measures available and considered more appropriate. Emphasized also US view that
                    consultations with <gloss target="#t_CP1">CP</gloss>s under Article XII should
                    begin at once.</p>
                <p>Meurice said he wld give this his immediate attention and wld take up with
                    Suetens, chief Belg del <gloss target="#t_GATT1">GATT</gloss>. He expressed
                    general understanding of problem and was already familiar with general outlines
                    of situation.</p>
                <p>Dept pass Ottawa; sent Dept 536, rptd info Ottawa unnumbered, Geneva 27 (for
                        <gloss target="#t_GATT1">GATT</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_Del1">Del</gloss>), Paris 117.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Millard</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
